      • readMapFromFile

        static java.util.Map<CellCoordinates,java.lang.Integer> readMapFromFile(java.lang.String name,
                                                                        int xOffset,
                                                                        int yOffset)
        Reads map from a file. Used in GUI to insert structures. Offset is used to place structure from file in a specific position selected by user.
        Parameters:
        name - a file name without .txt
        xOffset - x axis offset
        yOffset - y axis offset
        Returns:
        map of CellCoordinates and values
        See Also:
        GameOfLife.convert(Map), WireWorld.convert(Map)
